parts.text:
<OUTPUT_TEXT>
TASK – Prepare for trial by performing tasks such as organizing exhibits, which includes: developing comprehensive exhibit lists with descriptions, proposed use, and status; preparing multiple sets of exhibit binders for the judge, opposing counsel, and trial team; Bates-stamping and ensuring all exhibits are clearly marked and legible; coordinating with the attorney to identify and prepare demonstrative exhibits (e.g., timelines, charts); compiling witness binders containing relevant deposition transcripts and exhibits; assembling comprehensive trial notebooks for the attorney, including pleadings, motions, orders, witness lists, exhibit lists, jury instructions, and outlines for opening/closing statements; confirming witness availability, coordinating subpoenas, and arranging for their travel/lodging as needed; arranging for necessary courtroom technology and support (e.g., projectors, screens, court reporter, videographer); and maintaining a master trial calendar, tracking all deadlines and court appearances.
</OUTPUT_TEXT>
